      "writtenOn": "2019-10-29T01:15:23Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "This might be a bit confusing without knowing how test outputs are copied back...\n\nremoteOutDir is not the final destination of test output files; final destination is ResDir. Remote tests write output files to remoteOutDir/\u003ctest-name\u003e, and after they finish, Tast moves them to ResDir/\u003ctest-name\u003e.\n\nThis may sound cumbersome, but at this moment we do in this way for two reasons:\n1. To align copy-back logic between local tests and remote tests\n2. To prevent tests from overwriting log.txt\n\nSo at the end of tests, remoteOutDir should be empty.\n\nPlease let me update the comment slightly.",
